Package gnu.statistics

Interface Summary
Function This interface gives the requirements for a function.
Monotonicity For a given value of x, indicate if the function is monotonic increasing or monotonic decreasing as x is larger and larger.
ProbabilityDistribution This interface gives the requirements for a statistical distribution.
 

Class Summary
BinomialDistribution This class gives a Binomial distribution with n values of probability p.
BinomialMonotonicity For a given value of x, indicate if the function is monotonic increasing or monotonic decreasing as x is larger and larger.
CDF This is a Cumulative Distribution Function.
ContinuousDistribution This interface gives the requirements for a statistical distribution with a discrete random variable.
ContinuousFunction This interface gives the requirements for a continuous function.
ContinuousPMF This is a Probability mass function.
ContinuousX f(x) = x
ContinuousX2 f(x) = x^2
CountedSet A counted set maps numeric values to counts, as in a histogram or poisson distribution.
DiscreteDistribution This interface gives the requirements for a statistical distribution with a discrete random variable.
DiscreteFunction This interface gives the requirements for a discrete function.
DiscretePMF This is a Probability mass function.
DiscreteX f(x) = x
DiscreteX2 f(x) = x^2
Expectation This is the expectation value for a distribution.
PoissonMonotonicity For a given value of x, indicate if the function is monotonic increasing or monotonic decreasing as x is larger and larger.
Statistics This class gives a Binomial distribution with n values of probability p.
Variance This is the Variance for a distribution.
 

Exception Summary
DistributionNotContinuous Exception to indicate a discrete distribution is required.
DistributionNotDiscrete Exception to indicate a discrete distribution is required.
